### getStaticProps Overview

`getStaticProps` is a Next.js function that fetches data at **build time** and pre-renders the page as static HTML. It runs on the server and is never exposed to the client.

### Basic Usage

```jsx
export async function getStaticProps() {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/posts');
  const posts = await res.json();

  return {
    props: {
      posts,
    },
  };
}

export default function Blog({ posts }) {
  return (
    <ul>
      {posts.map(post => (
        <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

### Context Parameter

`getStaticProps` receives a context object with:

- `params` — route parameters for dynamic routes
- `preview` — preview mode flag
- `previewData` — preview mode data
- `locale` — active locale
- `locales` — supported locales
- `defaultLocale` — default locale

### Revalidate (ISR)

Add `revalidate` to enable Incremental Static Regeneration:

```jsx
export async function getStaticProps() {
  const data = await fetchData();

  return {
    props: { data },
    revalidate: 60, // Regenerate at most once every 60 seconds
  };
}
```

### When to Use SSG

Use `getStaticProps` when:

- Content is fetchable at build time
- Data doesn't change frequently
- SEO is important
- Fast page load is critical
- CMS, blog, marketing pages

### notFound and redirect

Return `notFound: true` for 404 pages or `redirect` for redirects:

```jsx
export async function getStaticProps({ params }) {
  const post = await getPost(params.id);

  if (!post) {
    return { notFound: true };
  }

  if (post.external) {
    return {
      redirect: { destination: post.externalUrl, permanent: false },
    };
  }

  return { props: { post } };
}
```

codeExample:
export async function getStaticProps({ params }) {
  try {
    const post = await fetch(`https://api.example.com/posts/${params.id}`).then(r => {
      if (!r.ok) throw new Error('Not found');
      return r.json();
    });

    return {
      props: { post },
      revalidate: 3600,
    };
  } catch {
    return { notFound: true };
  }
}

export default function Post({ post }) {
  return (
    <article>
      <h1>{post.title}</h1>
      <div>{post.content}</div>
    </article>
  );
}
